The paper deals with generating images from scene descriptions, which is a problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using recurrent networks and graph convolutional networks, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of generative adversarial networks, which is a popular topic in computer graphics (cs.GR). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing, as it deals with generating images from text descriptions (cs.CL).
